                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13682983" author="mpercy" created="Fri, 14 Jun 2013 01:11:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On this one, it would be better to use the pattern where you create a new server socket on port 0, query it to find the port assigned by the OS, then close the socket. Use that port in the test. The OS will not assign that port again right away and you are guaranteed to be able to use it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See the findFreePort() utility function in the embedded agent test:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flume/blob/trunk/flume-ng-embedded-agent/src/test/java/org/apache/flume/agent/embedded/TestEmbeddedAgent.java#L180&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flume/blob/trunk/flume-ng-embedded-agent/src/test/java/org/apache/flume/agent/embedded/TestEmbeddedAgent.java#L180&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13691435" author="mpercy" created="Sun, 23 Jun 2013 10:58:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is causing test failures also such as &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/flume-trunk/447/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/flume-trunk/447/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13691436" author="mpercy" created="Sun, 23 Jun 2013 11:08:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching updated patch, I&apos;m going to commit this as part of my 1.4 RM duties.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13691437" author="mpercy" created="Sun, 23 Jun 2013 11:11:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just pushed this to trunk and flume-1.4 branches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13691444" author="hudson" created="Sun, 23 Jun 2013 12:00:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in flume-trunk #448 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/flume-trunk/448/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/flume-trunk/448/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
